e ratio), pod_processes P99 dropped from 2.0 to 1.0 (66.67% change ratio) indicating potential pod restart or crash\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"frontend-2\",\n      \"reason\": \"Frontend service experiencing high response time degradation with rrt_max P99 increasing by 34.04%\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max P99 increased from 393093.1 to 278749.76 (34.04% change ratio), running on node aiops-k8s-08 which shows improved memory availability\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Analysis Summary:**\n\nThe primary root cause appears to be **TiDB KV storage layer performance issues** (tidb-tikv), with significant increases in `region_pending` (164.14%) and `cpu_usage` P99 (104.18%). This database-level bottleneck is likely causing cascading effects on application services.\n\n**Secondary issues:**\n- **redis-cart-0 pod instability**: The `pod_cpu_usage` and `pod_processes` metrics suggest this pod may have restarted or crashed during the fault period\n- **Frontend service degradation**: Frontend services are experiencing increased response times, likely due to downstream database performance issues\n\n**Key supporting evidence:**\n- TiDB metrics show the most significant changes (region_pending +164.14%)\n- No major Node-level resource constraints detected\n- Application service metrics (rrt_max, rrt) show moderate degradation consistent with database performance issues"}
